  "body": "## Scope\n\nThis Draft PR implements the bounded activation foundation for `PROMPT-QUALITY-MIGRATION-EXECUTION-PROGRAM`, preserves the existing `PRF-001` through `PRF-009` repairs, and registers `Repository Implementation Assurance Lite` as bounded future architecture without implementing any substantive `PPQR-001` through `PPQR-015` deliverable.\n\n## Exact identity\n\n```yaml\nbase_branch: main\nbase_sha: 25bd3af631c17fbfda76a3cabcaa612dfdc11143\nhead_branch: agent/activate-prompt-quality-program\ncurrent_exact_head: c4bf2ae0250b0caa8eb99e567e966a9fffd2711b\nscope_revision: sha256:1547c9f41164ef39464d3b1bfe91c7762ae4110d6d27b7f4c1d23666e363c511\nchanged_paths_from_base: 28\ndeleted_files: 0\n```\n\n## Repository Implementation Assurance Lite registration\n\nThe latest bounded amendment changes only three already-authorized paths:\n\n- `planning/prompt-quality/prompt-quality-execution-program.v1.json`\n- `planning/PROMPT_QUALITY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md`\n- `planning/NEXT_WORK.md`\n\nNo new path, Domain, Task, schema, validator, fixture, routing behavior, model execution, target-repository gate, or substantive quality implementation was added.\n\nThe registered architecture is:\n\n```text\nimplementation-prompt.md\n+\nassurance-lite.yaml\n```\n\n`assurance-lite.yaml` is planned as one linked artifact containing requirements, risks, acceptance/evidence mappings, and an implementation-report contract. Prompt-Pipeline validation is explicitly structural only. It does not prove semantic correctness, target-repository enforcement, implementation completion, Merge readiness, exact-main validation, or zero defects.\n\nThe capability is mapped into the existing task sequence rather than creating a sixteenth Task:\n\n- `PPQR-001`: baseline defects and repair-cycle cost;\n- `PPQR-002`: adaptive selection for repository-modification consumer paths;\n- `PPQR-003` / `PPQR-004`: contract and structural rules;\n- `PPQR-005`: linked artifact rendering and prompt binding;\n- `PPQR-006`: non-blocking pilot corpus;\n- `PPQR-007`: bounded structural validator and diagnostics;\n- `PPQR-009`: risk-tier activation and cost measurement;\n- `PPQR-010`: held-out Quality Delta promotion decision;\n- `PPQR-012`: cross-domain containment;\n- `PPQR-015`: fallback protection.\n\nSimple requests retain the lightweight default path. The initial pilot does not require a target-repository validator. Downstream independent review remains `PR-Inspector`.\n\n## Preserved repair baseline\n\nThe branch retains the existing `PRF-001` through `PRF-009` governance and evidence hardening, including:\n\n- current repository Head binding;\n- verified evidence-carrier descendant handling;\n- main-target and owner-merge containment;\n- exact-main ancestry verification;\n- deterministic production mutation counting;\n- exact-head CI identity;\n- pinned `PR-Inspector v1.11.1` official-output boundary.\n\nThe Assurance Lite registration does not weaken or replace these controls.\n\n## Exact-head canonical CI\n\n```yaml\nworkflow_name: CI\nworkflow_id: 302284939\nrun_id: 29658213296\nrun_number: 339\nconclusion: success\nexact_tested_head: c4bf2ae0250b0caa8eb99e567e966a9fffd2711b\n```\n\nAll jobs succeeded:\n\n- `PEaC canonical exact-head CI` — `88116219718`\n- `Renderer Node 20.x exact-head` — `88116219699`\n- `Renderer Node 22.x exact-head` — `88116219703`\n- `PR-Inspector v1.11.1 official-output boundary` — `88116219692`\n\nArtifacts:\n\n| Artifact | ID | Digest |\n|---|---:|---|\n| `exact-head-ci-identity` | `8433523363` | `sha256:79f8970e630fdfff8af0a11deded23a404d42386818e5e1892e6fdbac5cf7be2` |\n| `exact-head-renderer-evidence` | `8433523544` | `sha256:fa4b5693353c76fb26e24261faa23a253d4383c119214d5785f400bc90b4f9a9` |\n| `prompt-pipeline-kb-bundle` | `8433523727` | `sha256:a1141db473d1adaf9acb5fb35e8d0e64355f3599fd45ea66a9c70c57eca24d76` |\n| `official-output-boundary-evidence` | `8433517102` | `sha256:97921ac5bba96d16bdfdaf964678a2f0febea0ccaa283bf85c190cf88f4a49f0` |\n\n## Boundaries and non-effects\n\n```yaml\nquality_credit: false\nmigration_promotion_effect: none\nproduction_authority_effect: none\nrelease_readiness_claim: false\nproduction_readiness_claim: false\nlegacy_retirement_effect: none\nsubstantive_task_implementation: none\nassurance_lite_implementation: none\nmerge_performed: false\napproval_performed: false\ndeployment_performed: false\n```\n\n## Limitations\n\n- The PR is not merged; authoritative owner-Merge and exact-main evidence do not yet exist.\n- The Assurance Lite architecture is registered future work only and has not been evaluated against held-out repository tasks.\n- A successful CI run validates the repository at the exact Head; it does not replace fresh independent PR review.\n\n## Current status\n\n```yaml\ncurrent_exact_head_ci: PASS\ncurrent_exact_head: c4bf2ae0250b0caa8eb99e567e966a9fffd2711b\nfresh_pr_inspector_review: required\nmerge_readiness: not_claimed\n```\n\nThis PR must remain Draft and must not be merged until a fresh independent `PR-Inspector` review evaluates exact Head `c4bf2ae0250b0caa8eb99e567e966a9fffd2711b`.",
